GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Garth House makes its governing documents, conflict of interest policy and financial statements available to the public upon request.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Board members who find their interest in conflict with those of Garth House are required to disclose such conflict, abstain from any vote dealing with such matters, and if unable to serve as a loyal director, remove themselves from the Board.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11: Form 990 Review Process
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Form 990 is prepared by the outside accountant under the direction of the Executive Director. Upon completion, the Executive Director and outside accountant review and discuss.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 4: Description of Significant Changes to Organizational Documents
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Garth House amended their bylaws to create an Advisory Board of Directors and address voting by proxy with regards to a quorum.The Advisory Directors may attend meetings of the Board of Directors or the Executive Committee and may advise on any matter. The Advisory Directors may make motions, participate in discussions, and vote. Advisory Directors who participate in meetings serve as members of the Governing Board of the organization. However, Advisory Directors are not considered when determining whether a quorum exists. Further, Advisory Directors have no term limits or set term.Directors may vote by proxy; however attendance by proxy does not contribute to a quorum.
